description:
src/lib.rs:43 — `const BACKEND: &str = "doppler";` is at module scope. It's used by the type, the inventory submissions, and from_uri.

Idiomatic Rust associates such a const with the type:

    impl DopplerBackend {
        pub const NAME: &'static str = "doppler";
        ...
    }

then call sites use `DopplerBackend::NAME` (and the inventory blocks could even use `name: DopplerBackend::NAME,` to remove the duplication of the literal "doppler").

This is taste-only — there is no engineering difference. Filed as opinion.
